        "rich_text_rJaBdp": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>When people buy solitaire jewellery, the first thing they notice is the diamond - its size, sparkle, and shape. But there’s another detail that quietly makes a big difference: the setting. The setting is the way the diamond is held in place on a ring, bracelet, or earring.</p><p>Two of the most common settings used in solitaire jewellery are prong settings and bezel settings. Both look beautiful, but they behave differently when it comes to sparkle, safety, and everyday wear.</p><p>At <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lucira Jewelry\">Lucira Jewelry</a>, we design pieces using both styles depending on the jewellery type. Some customers prefer the classic look of prongs, while others love the smooth, modern feel of bezel settings. Let’s understand the difference in a simple way so you can decide what works best for you.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qw7HLy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Is a Prong Setting and Why It Is So Popular for Solitaire Rings",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What Is a Prong Setting and Why It Is So Popular for Solitaire Rings</h2>",
            "custom_id": "what-is",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_f34KML": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/What_Is_a_Prong_Setting_and_Why_It_Is_So_Popular_for_Solitaire_Rings.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_A8fUE6": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Is a Prong Setting ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>A prong setting is the traditional way of holding a diamond. Small metal claws - called prongs - grip the diamond from different sides and hold it slightly above the band.</p><p>Most <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/solitaire-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"solitaire rings\">solitaire rings</a> use four or six prongs. The diamond sits higher than the metal, which means light can pass through the stone from many directions.</p><p>That’s why prong settings are known for giving diamonds more sparkle.</p>",
            "custom_id": "color",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_rtW66j": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "A Real Example from Lucira",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>A Real Example from Lucira</h3><p>Our 6 Prong Solitaire Stud 1.5 cts earrings are a good example of this design. The prongs hold the diamond securely while still showing almost the entire stone. Because there is very little metal covering the diamond, it catches light beautifully.</p><p>Another example is the Four Prongs Emerald-Cut Solitaire Engagement Ring. The prongs simply hold the diamond at the corners, letting the clean shape of the emerald cut shine.</p><p>This style has been used in engagement rings for decades because it highlights the diamond in the most natural way.</p>",
            "custom_id": "a-real",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_AJHQPB": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Another example is the Four Prongs Emerald-Cut Solitaire Engagement Ring. The prongs simply hold the diamond at the corners, letting the clean shape of the emerald cut shine.</p><p>This style has been used in engagement rings for decades because it highlights the diamond in the most natural way.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_npCJMr": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Is a Bezel Setting and Why Many People Prefer It for Everyday Jewellery",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What Is a Bezel Setting and Why Many People Prefer It for Everyday Jewellery</h2>",
            "custom_id": "what-is-a",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_KifUpC": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/What_Is_a_Bezel_Setting_and_Why_Many_People_Prefer_It_for_Everyday_Jewellery.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bPcnFE": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>A bezel setting works a little differently. Instead of claws holding the diamond, a thin rim of metal surrounds the stone and keeps it in place.</p><p>The diamond sits inside this metal frame, which makes the jewellery look smooth and modern.</p><p>Because the edges of the diamond are covered, bezel settings are often considered one of the safest and most durable settings.</p><h3>A Real Example from Lucira</h3><p>Take our Round Diamond Bezel Set Tennis Bracelet. Each diamond is surrounded by a thin metal border that protects the stone and keeps it secure. The bracelet also feels smooth against the wrist because there are no raised prongs.</p><p>Another design is the Full Bezel Round <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/diamond-tennis-bracelets\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Diamond Tennis Bracelet\">Diamond Tennis Bracelet</a>, where every diamond is completely enclosed. This makes it a great option for jewellery that you want to wear often.</p><p>Bezel settings are especially common in bracelets and daily-wear rings.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bhGzpc": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "A Simple Comparison Between Bezel and Prong Diamond Settings",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>A Simple Comparison Between Bezel and Prong Diamond Settings</h2><p>Here’s an easy way to see the difference between the two settings.</p>",
            "custom_id": "a-simple",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
