        "rich_text_qwTzXx": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Both settings work well - it really depends on what you prefer.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_mEE3FU": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Many Solitaire Engagement Rings Use Prong Settings",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Why Many Solitaire Engagement Rings Use Prong Settings</h2>",
            "custom_id": "why-many",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_mJNMBM": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Why_Many_Solitaire_Engagement_Rings_Use_Prong_Settings.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_pJNxxc": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>If you look at most engagement rings, you’ll notice they often use prongs. The reason is simple: they show off the diamond.</p><p>Because the diamond sits higher and is not covered by much metal, light enters from different angles. This gives the stone more brilliance.</p><p>At Lucira, pieces like our Four-Prong Princess Cut Diamond Stud Earrings use minimal metal so the diamond becomes the star of the design.</p><p>Another advantage is that prong settings can make the diamond look slightly larger, because the stone is more visible.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qPAdyV": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Bezel Settings Are Perfect for Jewellery You Wear Every Day",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Why Bezel Settings Are Perfect for Jewellery You Wear Every Day</h2>",
            "custom_id": "why-bezel",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_q6f8nd": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Why_Bezel_Settings_Are_Perfect_for_Jewellery_You_Wear_Every_Day.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_JjwgUx": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>While prongs are beautiful, bezel settings are known for being strong and practical.</p><p>Since the diamond is surrounded by metal, it’s less likely to get chipped or loosened. That’s why many people choose bezel settings for jewellery they wear frequently.</p><p>For example, Lucira’s Celeste Round Tennis Bracelet and Round Radiant Tennis Bracelet are designed for comfortable daily wear. The diamonds stay secure while still giving the bracelet a refined look.</p><p>Another advantage is comfort. Without prongs, the jewellery doesn’t snag on clothes or hair.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_AEV4Yg": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Do Prong or Bezel Settings Make a Diamond Look Bigger?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Do Prong or Bezel Settings Make a Diamond Look Bigger?</h2>",
            "custom_id": "do-prong",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_hD9nPa": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Do_Prong_or_Bezel_Settings_Make_a_Diamond_Look_Bigger.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_ygpmim": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Many buyers ask this question.</p><p>Prong settings usually make the diamond appear a bit larger, because you can see more of the stone.</p><p>Bezel settings frame the diamond with metal, so the stone might look slightly smaller. But the clean frame often creates a bold and stylish design.</p><p>In fact, many modern jewellery lovers prefer the bezel look because it feels sleek and contemporary.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
